Welcome back to Wall Power, my private email detailing the inner
workings of the art world. I=E2=80=99m Marion Maneker.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Tonight, my thoughts on the new Caspar David Friedrich retrospective openin=
g at the Met this week. There are many ways to look at Friedrich=E2=80=94an=
 important artist who is not well known in the United States, despite casti=
ng a long and complex shadow over both American art history and popular cul=
ture. You=E2=80=99ll know Friedrich
from the meme-able painting Wanderer above the Sea of Fog, but there=E2=80=
=99s a great deal more to think about given the nationalist political momen=
t in which this show opens.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

But first, Julie Davich has a few notes from around town=E2=80=A6

Julie Brener Davich
Julie Brener Davich

* The
whimsical wares of Iris Apfel: =E2=80=9CI didn=E2=80=99t give a damn about =
going to the party or being at the party,=E2=80=9D Iris Apfel said in the 2=
014 documentary about her life. It was about =E2=80=9Cgetting dressed for t=
he party.=E2=80=9D A fashion and interior design influencer before that was=
