kYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVdhbGwrUG93ZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgyJTJG=
MTElMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIj=
oiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA3MDgwOX0/5b05a36ec8a5ba5d8154d=
5aa7098ab1bad4e778c98299b356cf78c776d524b69" style=3D"text-decoration:under=
line;color:#d40000;">segment of the donor class</a>. Art, like politics, ha=
s a small but vital constituency that often determines what takes place mor=
e than the public, itself.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>That said, =
this is
not a case of elite mandarins mounting a show of little interest to the ple=
bs. Friedrich=E2=80=99s contemplative wanderer atop his rocky promontory ha=
s been grafted into numerous alternative contexts, from futuristic panorama=
s to apocalyptic hellscapes to riffs on everything from <em>Star Wars</em> =
to manga. There=E2=80=99s clearly something about German romanticism that r=
esonates two centuries later. Like the romantics, we live in an era of over=
whelming technological and political upheaval, and often want to
believe that there is something more that animates our spirits. And, just a=
s in Friedrich=E2=80=99s day, there are overtly political purposes to this =
distraction from our rational abilities.=C2=A0</p></div>
