=80=9D this person wrote. =E2=80=9CIn theory it could help increase G.D.P. =
if the government maintains stable spending by being more efficient. So thi=
s could
actually be good for the art world=E2=80=A6=E2=80=9D I had to explain to th=
is person that there is no distinction between good spending and bad spendi=
ng in regards to calculating G.D.P. So cutting $2 trillion in =E2=80=9Cwast=
eful spending=E2=80=9D would still cause the economy to significantly contr=
act.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">For the record, I would love to see the bu=
dget, and its deficit, reduced substantially. But that has to be done legal=
ly and
responsibly, not as a $2 trillion shock. (Which is one reason, among others=
, these current efforts are not likely to be successful. Let=E2=80=99s hope=
=2E) That said, I did want to remind yo=
u all that I love hearing from you. I=
=E2=80=99m always happy to concede my ignorance and mistakes. If you want t=
o tell me I=E2=80=99m wrong, or if there=E2=80=99s anything you think I mis=
sed, simply reply to this email. I=E2=80=99ll write you back. Or use +1.917=
